{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"36a78606-0fa2-4492-a77f-280149c679af","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the MTP runner package:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"1.5.0\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test executable directly (MTP builds your test project as a standalone app).\n\nThat's the core migration. The `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest. If you're on .NET SDK 9.0.200+, you can alternatively set `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` (the older property name still works too).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"721b4ed2-8eae-4bdf-bbe4-3590d614df5f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":336,"requestId":"0433:3FE43:1F539A4:23196A9:69E81953"},"id":"bd2f9336-988d-452c-9e98-b471e7dfcad4","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:42:02.799Z","parentId":"6b1b4dd2-3601-49cb-9b51-45ab396678b4"}
